          "date": "2014-07-25 13:24:07.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Liang Zhen",
          "email": "liang.zhen@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-07-31 07:01:27.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-0000 lnet: LNet drop rule implementation",
        "message": "LU-0000 lnet: LNet drop rule implementation\n\nThis is implementation of LNet Drop Rule, which can randomly drop\nLNet messages at specified rate.\n\nLNet Drop Rule can only be applied to receive side of message. User\ncan add drop_rule either on end point of cluster (client/server) or\non LNet routers.\n\nHere are lctl command to control LNet Drop Rules:\n- net_drop_add src dst rate [delay]\n  add Drop Rule from @src to @dst at rate @rate\n\n- net_drop_del src dst\n  remove all drop rules from @src to @dst\n\n- net_drop_list\n  list all drop rules on current node\n\nExamples:\n- lctl net_drop_add o2ib0 192.168.1.102@tcp 1000\n  add new drop rule, it will drop 1/1000 messages from network o2ib0\n  to 192.168.1.102@tcp\n\n- lctl net_drop_add 10.8.6.123@o2ib1 * 500\n  add new drop rule, it will drop 1/500 messages from 10.8.6.123@o2ib1\n  to all targets\n\nSigned-off-by: Liang Zhen <liang.zhen@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I3dbd00ecf5fcbcbedf7e0c1e5868a3780958df70\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
